<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 07 at 8:41AM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern
Pittsburg County through 915 AM CDT...
At 840 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 6 miles
southwest of Ashland, moving east at 45 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects.
Locations in or near the path include...
Kiowa...                          Savanna...
Ashland...                        Blanco...
Pittsburg...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 200 PM CDT for
southeastern Oklahoma.</instruction>
